description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join the IT Service Desk team at the Royal Liverpool and Broadgreen NHS Trust. The Service Desk is the first point of contact for all trust staff and you will be expected to provide both 1st and 2nd Line IT Support.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is a demanding post which requires excellent interpersonal and organisational skills and the ability to communicate well at all levels.&lt;br /&gt;You will need to demonstrate a professional and helpful approach with excellent telephone and communication skills, whilst ensuring customers needs are satisfied. A flexible working approach is essential as is the need to work well under pressure and you will need to be a good team player.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The team handles a high volume of calls each day and the ability to adapt to change is essential.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be highly motivated and be able to work in accordance with ITIL standards taking calls, resolving incidents/service requests and managing emails and webforms.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will ideally have previously worked in an NHS IT Service Delivery or Service Desk environment and skills should include a sound knowledge of Microsoft products and Active Directory administration, an interest in solving problems and end to end customer service is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMark JonesJob titleService Desk ManagerEmail addressMark.Jones@LiverpoolFT.nhs.ukTelephone number0151 706 5499Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
